Content: Loving the thin crust but very upset that the thick is now mostly bread with very little sauce and cheese What the hell happened the carmelized crust is like crack cocaine  you will do anything snow sleet or rain to get there to get your fix service is great  love hearing Foreigner and Journey blasting

Author: Josie F.
Content: OK Â This is one of those Chicago spots you must try Â It is not about the service or the atmosphere Â The pizza is the best in the city Â Hands down Â Four of us went to lunch for 33 bucks plus tip Â We each had a Â personal deep dish and a drink Â It was so reasonable I thought it could have been a mistake Â  We called ahead of time to place our order Â Our pizza was on the table five minutes after we sat Â If you think the pizza is burned you really do not know food and do not get the concept Â If you bothered to eat the caramelized Â crust you would taste the light sweetness and great texture it brings Â Keep up the great work

Author: Michelle D.
Content: While the Morton Grove location has more character more mom and pop feel the pizza is still the same Â Great place and good atmosphere they renovated a few years ago so it is now filled with plasma tvs Â The pizza is excellent Â We always get the deep dish sausage green pepper and onion and are never disappointed Â Make sure you try the crust Â It may look burnt but it is really just carmelized cheese Â It is in a good location so you could catch a movie at Webster just before or after since the theatre is right across the street Â I highly recommend

Author: Corrie N.
Content: I dont know what they do but the crust is magic Â Magic I tell you

Author: Kathleen O.
Content: EXCELLENT deep dish pizzayum

Author: Gino T.
Content: This stuff is flame Dont sleep on this joint you tourist will regret it Mouth watering pizza and a really smooth atmosphere will make wish you were born in such a city This place is where real headz come and chill and enjoy a slice or two Dont come to Chicago and not come to this place Located in the center of yuppie ville no need to worry about the neighborhood just watch out for there delivery guys

Author: Andrew L.
Content: Good deep dish pizza and service Â The plain pie had a good sauce and flavor toppings like sausage are definitely the way to go

Author: Natalie G.
Content: Im going to go out on a limb here and say this is 10 times better than Ginos 5 times better that Giordanos and just a tid bit better than Lou Malnatis Â If you want good deep dish come here it is awesome and the crust is just a little burnt to perfectness Â I will be coming here from now on for my pizza needs which mean a lot Â It also has a better atmosphere than the other pizza joints Lous in Lincoln Park feels like a basement which makes it only even better Â GREAT PIZZA

Author: Jennie M.
Content: ok so here is my thing about PequodsIm a New York Pizza kind of girl Give me a slice loaded with veggies and meat that I have to fold in half and shove in my mouth for it to fit all for like under 3 bucks and Im in Pizza Heaven Ive lived in Chicago for 4 and a half years and have only had deep dish twice because frankly to me there is something wrong with having to eat pizza with a fork and knife But I will tell you that twice that deep dish has been Pequods Side note why the HELL do you midwesterners cut your thin crust pizza in SQUARES That is the worst thing I have ever seen That has no bearing on this review I just felt the need to mention it Now back to Pequods I like their pizza but its not life altering as so many of these other reviews state If someone comes from out of town and wants deep dish Ill probably take them here over some other deep dish place but Its not my beall endall pizza place like Rays Pizza in NYC is

Author: Mark K.
Content: There is deep dish pizza and well there is Pequods Â I love this pizza Â I usually get a sausage and mushroom deep dish Â The trademark of a Pequods pizza is the carmelized crust Â I absolutely love it and this place is my first and foremost recommendation to all visitors to Chicago Â Now there is plenty of pizza to choose from but the combination of sauce great tasting sausage and carmelized crust makes this one of the many reasons I miss Chicago

Author: Michael H.
Content: Although the name is unusual they have great pan pizza and a nice comfortable atmosphere It is what you would expect when you think of a pizzeria Allow 30 minutes for the pizza and then go see a movie across the street

Author: Alexander C.
Content: Think thick crust with a layer of cheese toppings and sauce on top Â This is not like a Lous or Unos but something a little different Â Great crust Â I read about the caramelized crust edges and I immediately became a fan Â We went early on a Saturday and were ushered up stairs Â The upstairs had all of the young families and was a bit loud with the kids running around Â I wish this place delivered to me

Author: michael r.
Content: Not much to say except its the best deep dish pizza around You have to order the pepperoni the cheese is carmelized on top and the combo is fantastic Dont bother with the thin crust its average at best

Author: Jen H.
Content: I am not a Chicago native and tend to waiver between thin and thick crust pizza depending on the day One thing I can say about about Pequods that makes it stand out from the crowdtheir thick crust pizza has a ring of burnt cheese which is absolutely delicious and unlike any other pizza Also their sign has a fish with a thong on his head 4 stars for that aloneFor an appetizertry the fried zucchini

Author: Jeremy T.
Content: This was a very disappointing experience because heard good things about Pequods Unfortunately that wasnt our experience It took us an hour to get a SMALL THIN crust pizza and when we got it it was burned Wed have sent it back but we didnt have another hour to wait See the picture attached for the burn evidence

Author: Alex V.
Content: I flew out to Chicago to seek out Deep dish pizza and I found it Went to Burts Place in Morton Grove it was like so what I was so fired up for Burts that was a major reason I flew out So I got back on with my fellow yelpers in Chicago and you guys made my trip worth it with Pequods Pizza Pequods was night  day super tasty Thanks Chicago By the way Wrigley Field was awesome too Respect

Author: Matt P.
Content: My favorite of the nonchain pizzerias Â Their pizza is the bomb Â However I liked it better when it was this hole in the wall place with about 6 tables  now its a family affair Â Good for them but like many old fuddy duddies I become nostalgic for what was

Author: caroline k.
Content: Man this place is real chi deep dish done right Â Not like those of the better known ie Ginos Giordanos Lous etc I brought an out of towner hoping to show him deep dish at its best Â  Â A bit lighter ie less cheese and dough this place is by far the best deep dish Ive had Â We had a medium pan topped with spinach mushrooms canadian bacon and sausage and could barely finish more than half Â  Note leftover pizza that evening wasnt quite as good I think its best enjoyed on the spot Â  Definitely will be back here for more Â Staff is friendly and quick to refill drinks Â Love it

Author: Mike D.
Content: Pequods deep dish pizza can be summed up in three words BEST PIZZA EVER

Author: Tommy D.
Content: Yes This pizza is excellent The thick crust is great but the thin crust is my faveand its one of very few pizzas my girlfriend and I can agree on The crust is awesome not too thin but not too thick The sauce is sweet and plentiful If you eat at the restaurant please notice the neon whale wearing womens panties on his head NICE

Author: Danielle C.
Content: This was the first time Id been here in a very long time over 7 yrs ago Â We went on a Saturday night which also happened to be St Pattys day weekend The place was packed w loud  drunk depaul kids and we got seated after about 15 minutes The pizza was well worth it though My boyfriend and I ordered the medium thin cruststill awesome after all these years Id definitely recommend

Author: Emily P.
Content: My new favorite pizza in Chicago

Author: emily h.
Content: I am a huge pizza whore and decided to have my sons first birthday party at Pequods I love their pizza especially the deep It is the rare deep but not stuffed kind and knew they had a nice sized party room Â At first I was feeling a little guilty that maybe it was a selfish decision but after having a successful birthday bash there all guilt was gone Â The pizza service and value were all great Â Maybe parties at Pequods will be a new birthday tradition

Author: Brian P.
Content: the wait was ridiculousthe pizza is so fluffythe water tastes disgustingthe soda wasnt that sweettwo slices filled me up very welli would go there againoh leftovers tasted better

Author: Emily W.
Content: Sweet Jesus this pizza is even better as leftovers Â The burnt cheese is unreal Â Our original order was on Monday I enjoyed some of it Tuesday at home in CA and on Friday and both were FANTASTIC

Author: David A.
Content: Another top 5 Pizza Place great location and good service Â I have been here more than a few times for in restaurant dining as well as takeout Â This place has great prices and again some of the best pizza in the city Â I highly recommend this place if you are trying to find the best of Chicago

Author: Carly L.
Content: My desert island pizza if thats even a thing I definitely miss the smokefilled nonbiance from the prefire prereremodel days but the pizzas still delicious and worth suffering through Lincoln Park for Five stars for the pizza minus one for not delivering to Logan Square Cmon guys get it together Were dying out here

Author: chris c.
Content: i am giving it 4 stars because normally this is 5 star pizza but the last time I was in admittedly it was the most packed it has ever been while i was there was average at best I have had many good experiences there before with their perfect crust great sauce and generous tasty toppings Not sure what happened when i was there last but I guess even the best have an off night

Author: A H.
Content: We went here to try out some deep dish for the first time since moving to Chicago It doesnt look like much from the outside but this place is two stories with plenty of room for everyone For starters the Pequod Salad is delicious with plenty of fresh veggies and cheese slices cut into the shape of fish I dont know why theyre cut into the shape of fish but it was cute The salad is plenty big for two people to share The deep dish or pan pizza was amazing We split a small one between the two of us and we were both stuffed when we left Its a build your own cheese pizza and we added sausage and spinach to it The best part about the pizza was the crust It was the perfect crust Add in the friendly quick staff and you have an excellent pizza place

Author: Eric V.
Content: Ive been here a couple of times now and am finally getting around to reviewing it Â My first impression is that is a fine place Â Aesthetically speaking theres nothing phenomenal about it Â Its a quaint exposed brick pizza  sports bar Â We ordered salad hot wings garlic bread and a few different pan pizzas Â I cant say I have anything bad to say about the food accommodations or service however nothing really jumped out as fantastic Â The wings were by far the best thing I ate there Â The pizza was far from unique and lacking in bold flavor Â I was drawn to add several condiments to each slice to bring out the flavor a bit Â Not bad just not great Â Id go back if a group decided on the place but I cant see myself choosing this place for myself Â Again Im giving this place 3 stars instead of 2 because I realize how wide the range of pizza appreciation spans

Author: Charlene S.
Content: I wasnt impressed the first time I had it it was a few years ago and Id never gone back Â Im a Lou Malnatis girl Â But my patients LOVE this place and talked it up this week so I decided to try it again Â The hubs and I called it in and ordered their deep dish pan same thing and ordered sausage mushrooms onions and jalapenos Â It was ready on time and we drove home with the intoxicating smell radiating from the back seat Â I was excited Â It looked amazing and we hung out watching the Bulls game sitting in our family room and devoured a couple slices Â You had to use a fork and knife it was quite a meal Â The melted cheesy charred crust the humongoid sausages the generous pizza sauce Â It was delicious Â We finally found another deep dish pizza that we enjoy Â The ingredients were fresh and abundant Â Damn Pequods youve redeemed yourself

Author: Joanne N.
Content: Nice place in a great location Their pizza is pretty decent Ive tried their thin crust as well as their deep dish which is bready as opposed to Giordarnos which has no shortage of cheese Ive had a few people recommend this place to me and tell me how life changing it would be With the bar already set so high I cant really say I was blown away Satisfied with my meal and the price I paid for it Yes I can see myself eating here again

Author: Das Y.
Content: Best deep dish pizza in Chicago Good service and atmosphere Only reason it is not 5 is because the appertizers were poor quality

Author: Dustin L.
Content: DO NOT EAT Â I have lived in Lincoln Park for approximately 9 years and this place is horrible Â Everyone keeps telling me how good it is and Ive tried it multiple times Â Not so Â The crust is usually burnt and the service is beyond bad Â Buyer beware

Author: Jenny B.
Content: Best pan pizza Ive had in a long time Delicious crust and reasonable prices This is a must try

Author: John-Paul E.
Content: I just love this place The crust is amazing and there lunch specials are great 500 for a big slice of pizza and beverage of choice Beer included Where else in this city can you get lunch for such a deal

Author: Sam G.
Content: Great pizza good beers

Author: e e.
Content: good pizza good atmosphere ive tried the famous deep dish with caramelized cheesey crust stuff some of the best deep dish ive had im not a 100 fan of deep dishthe restaurant from the outside looks a little iffy but inside is clean updated cozy and buzzing with a crowd of down to earth people Â the wait staff is friendly and quick apps are good and prices are exactly what you want to pay when going out for pizzagoing here is very comfortable and relaxed and then you get GOOD PIZZAthin looked good too thats next weekends dinner

Author: Ismael M.
Content: I have never eaten AT Pequods only ordered out Â I would have to say hands down this is the best deep dish pizza in chicago Â The sauce is perfect and the crust is to die for Â Usually when you eat a deep dish pizza the crust at the end is this flaky cookie like substance that tastes OK but is not as good as the rest of the pizza Â Pequods carmalizes their crust and has the deep dish meat of the center of the pizza go all the way to the end Â You get a carmalized sweet treat Â How often would you say that the crust is the best part of the pizza when the pizza is already good

Author: John K.
Content: Pequods deep dish pizzas have the best pizza crust in the world Â Not in Chicago Â Not in the USA Â The world

Author: Meg C.
Content: This is my favorite pizzeria and I absolutely love the carmelized crust Â Love the sausage pepperoni and mushroom pizza

Author: Rahul S.
Content: Ok I live in Morton Grove and there happens to be a Pequod here Â However I wanted to go to Lincoln Park and hang out there Â When I was entered there I was wondering why the lights were off Â That was weird Â I guess it must be a recession or something Â But anyways the first slice I ate was a 355 Â But for some weird reason the second piece was a 45 Â I guess Im used to eating UNOs or Ginos East Â I dont know Â But its still pretty good

Author: Nikhil M.
Content: My friend Tony took me to this place when we were in the area saying he goes there all the time for their lunch special For the prize the pizza was worth it Sad to hear about the owners daughter though My condolences

Author: johnny b.
Content: Best deep dish in the city and I dont even really like deep dish but this is great

Author: Jim W.
Content: Pequods was ok I noticed it while sitting in a bookstore across the street and decided to give it a try The atmosphere was fun  both booths and tall tables to choose from The service was also quick attentive and polite They had a good beer selection as well I was disappointed by their pan pizza however It was advertised by Pequods and by readers on yelp as a deep dish pizza However I found that the only thing deep about it was the crust  there was a lot of bread with very little cheese and marinara on top not what Ive come to expect from a deep dish Also the veggies on top did not look or taste fresh although a second pie with only cheese tasted a bit better

Author: Cristina G.
Content: I looooooove Pequods We always order the New York style pepperoni extra pepperoni please and a salad with ranchseriously the best pizza Ive ever had

Author: Matt H.
Content: Im not a big fan of Chicago style deep dish but I do like Pequods Â I think it might have to do with them never cleaning the grease and gunk out of their deep dish pans which makes the crust extra greasy and crisp Â Also big fan of the burnt cheese Â The only problem is is that I always have horrible indigestion after going here Â I would never eat pizza here and then go out drinking for the night without a 2 hour pit stop at home

Author: Erin T.
Content: Pequods has the sickest lunch special in all the land  for 5 you can get a personal pan pizza and a drink soda or beer Â These personal pan pizzas have a divine and addictive caramelized crust  crispy and a little burnt and so damn good youll crave it for weeks Â It is really a good thing I left the contract job I had down the street because otherwise my health would be in serious jeopardy from daily pizza consumption Â The Pequods lunch special is a sometimes food

Author: Joe P.
Content: This place was really good It was one of the best pizzas I have ever had I was on a road trip with some friends and we stopped in Chicago We ate at this place The toppings were really good We had a pan pizza with sausage The caramelized crust was really good I approve of Chicago pizza

Author: Natalie T.
Content: The pizza was pretty good but I have to say that the atmosphere turned me off for some reason Â Cant put my finger on itwe were sat upstairs and the bathroom up there had Lord of the Ring paintings on the wall not that theres anything wrong with that

Author: Molly R.
Content: Chicago deep dish is wiggling all of its casserolelike goodness into my heart Â And Pequods is helping convert me into an official deep disher  tart tomato sauce burntcrust that was moist on the inside perfectly crunch on the outside and lotsandlotsocheese Â Unfortunately Pequods only offers design your own pies this is starting to seem like common practice in Chicago and notsomany topping options no unusual options or gourmet cheese choices but this is far made up for my their ahmazing 495 lunch deal Â 495 for a 7 1 topping pizza and a domestic macro pint Â I LOVE a good deal Â The smaller individually sized pizza means no sharing necessary Â No topping selection arguments between me and the bf And results in a pizza with a great crusttopie ratio Â YUM

Author: k e.
Content: By far the best deep dish Â The crust is delicious and the burnt cheese on the crust is mindblowing Â A sausage deepdish from here can turn any day around Â Its a little out of the way for outoftowners but way more worth the trip than going to Giordanos or Lou Malnattis if youre visiting Chicago

Author: Yaw N.
Content: It took me nearly four years of living in Chicago to discover one of its finest offerings in pizza Forget ginos easy or giodarnos Pequods is the best deep dish Ive had so far and its even worth the nearly two hour wait for delivery I loved the pepperoni and the sausage pizzas Ive had from here In case youre wondering they do deliver downtown so pick up your phone and place an order next time you want a good notsohealthy Chicago treat

Author: Robert B.
Content: First time going to Pequods Â I have been a big fan of Lou Malnotis so I was a little critical at first Â Well I have to say Pequods does do the key deep dish things right Â One the toppings are great Â We have pepperoni Sausage green peppers and onions Â The sauce was bland but let the toppings really shine out Â They also do this awesome thing with the cheese all the way to the edge of the crust Â This is really the best part Â Good service but just like any deep dish it takes a while to cook Â Be patient its worth it

Author: Suzanne M.
Content: Came into Pequods with my fiancÃ©e after losing yet another softball game We were bumming about our lack of softball prowess and pizza heals all wounds Pequods has a sports bar atmosphere a natural fit in a sporty town like Chicago but its clear that on game night this place is going to be packed Its a relatively small barrestaurant with short little booths made for two and barstool flanked tables surrounded by Chicago sports memorabilia and flatscreen TVs We kept it simple soda salad sausagespinachmushroom deep dish pie Our server brought our drinks and salads quickly service here is brisk and friendly The house salad was simple  chopped lettuce sliced black olives a slice of tomato shredded carrots all dressings on the side Comforting in its simplicity Our pizza took another 2025 minutes pretty standard for a deep dish place I was hesitant about getting deep dish because I cant stand the typical heavy buttery pastrydough crusts that so many Chicagostyle places employ When it came out I saw that the cheese had oozed out onto the sides of the wellseasoned cast iron skillet and I was briefly debating how greasy everything was going to be But yessssI was extremely pleasantly surprised at the lightness of the crust on Pequods pizza How Pequods can take a thick layer of tangy crunchyonthebottom but lightontheinside crust smother it with cheese bright tomato sauce and fresh spinach herby golfball sized chunks of sausage and fresh mushrooms and have it NOT be a belly bomb is kind of a pizza miracle I ate two slices of mediumsized pie and felt full without that greaseball quesiness I get from just one slice of the other guys stuff This just might be the best deep dish Ive had in ChicagoBased on pizza alone this place is 5 stars Id happily go back and have it again and againprovided theres no game on so I can avoid the crowds

Author: Dorothy M.
Content: I had a deep dish with mushroom spinach and sausage Its just average Nothing very special about the crust or the topping If anything the tomato sauce flavor is too overwhelming that it really doesnt matter what topping I put on there It just tastes like tomato The wheat beer I had 193 I think That was very good

Author: John R.
Content: Their pan pizza is fantastic Things I like about it Focaccialike Carmelized crust burnt mozzarella on the ends meatball sized sausage large ingredients and enough cheese and sauce to make is a chicagostyled pan pizza The sausage may have changed a little bit when Burt sold the place Its got a little more spice Its seems more like an italian sausage than a more mild sausage that is signature at Burts and other deepdish mainstays in chicagoThe restaurant has a good beerselection not the best in Lincoln Park but they have plenty of Microbrews The Clybourne location also has a second level so youre not going to wait long on the weekend The main floor has plenty of TVs and has a nice renovated interiorI also like that they put a sheet of tin foil over the pizza when you get carry out It really seems to trap in the heat I love watching the steam come out of the box when I open it

Author: Daniel S.
Content: Great lunch special

Author: Kate P.
Content: Best pizza in Chicago Love the burnt crust on the deep dish Yummo

Author: Allen R.
Content: I hadnt had Pequods Pizza in years it is just as awesome as I remembered Â It is good to know some things never change Â You know it is truly good pizza when the cheese pizza is a satisfying choice but when it come to toppings there is no skimping

Author: Kristen N.
Content: I was planning a day trip to Chicago and relied on Yelp for the best suggestions With over 900 reviews and still at 4 stars I assumed that this place was going to be superbWe walked in and there was a huge blast of heat pretty nice coming from the 30ish degree weather outside We were greeted rather quickly and sat instantly Our waitress was really nice and attentive I dont know her name but she is blonde if that helps PWe had the lunch special the personal deep dish pizzas garlic bread and jalapeÃ±o poppers for our apps I dont know if its just me or maybe we came on an off day but I felt like I have had much better pizza The jalapeÃ±o poppers and garlic bread were good but the pizza Maybe I just dont like Chicago pizza Maybe because it was the lunch special No idea but my boyfriend didnt really rave about it either

Author: Jenn C.
Content: I love this place Its a great place to go on a Saturday eveningBlackhawks bar Get there early because tables go fast

Author: Crisann S.
Content: Got the pan pizza to try out Chicago style pizza but didnt like the deep dish style Â I think Ill get the thin crust next time Â The sauce was pretty tomatoey and the sausage mixed in was pretty darn good Â The dark crust on the upper edge of the pizza was sooo delicious crispy and burnt looking but probably wont kill you if you dont eat it that often

Author: Jen D.
Content: Pequods pizza is just absolutely addicting Â There is typically not more than two weeks that I go without grabbing a pizza They always are filled to capacity so its pretty telling that they are a muchloved staple in Chicago

Author: Pearl B.
Content: Pequods Pizza is delicious Definitely an awesome Chicago pizza I absolutely loved the crust I couldnt give it 5 stars because I still think Lou Malnatis is my all time favorite

Author: Kristo E.
Content: This place is delicious The best deep dish Ive had by far

Author: Tom D.
Content: This place was amazing a line out the door and it was pouring rain dont be in a hurry if you order the pan pizza it takes a while but is so worth it in the end Just enjoy a few green lines while you wait

Author: Jen Y.
Content: Normally I go for pizza mainly for cheese and go for thin crust at most places but Pequods deep dish is amazing that youll be crazy not to get it Â Its already been said many times but the best part is the crispy cheesy crust Â I had a sausage and mushroom and it was heavenly delicious Â Ordered for pick up and it took 30 minutes Â Quick and easy Â Would love to come back and sit down to enjoy it while watching a game next time

Author: kathryn i.
Content: Favorite deepdish in Chicago

Author: Susan C.
Content: Another AMAZING pizza place if you enjoy deep dish deliciousness Â Great place if youre craving deep dish Â The wait is a bit long but it is well worth it Â I went a few weeks ago and split a medium deep dish with several toppings mushrooms onions black olives Â The pizza had about an inch thick of cheese on the top and the toppings are plentiful Â The sauce wasnt overly sweet but had very good flavor Â I would definitely recommend this place if you are in the area Â It will not disappoint

Author: Ryan H.
Content: I made the trek as a tourist from dtown Chicagojumped on red line  walked for 1520mins IT WAS WORTH IT Although the fried zucchini were just par for the course they keep me occupied while I wait the prerequisite 30 mins for good deep dish I ordered the pepp  sausage pan w caramelized crust and it did not disappoint Staff was friendly and the Official Blackhawks bar took me back to the Roenick  Chelios days Now if have to carry my leftovers back

Author: Sarah K.
Content: Pequods pizza doesnt taste like anyone elses pizza so theyve got that going for them which is nice But they had a fire a few years back and I dont think their pizza has been as good since I know this place gets great reviews and I just wanted to include my opinion because a friend went recently and was disappointed after reading so many glowing reviews Everyone has different taste in pizza and in my book Pequods pizza is just average

Author: K N.
Content: Awesome pizzagood atmospherelove itperiod

Author: P R.
Content: The best Deep dish Pizza in Chicago Â I cant say much else because thats pretty much all weve got there but we are always happy when we get pizza from herethe crust is AMAZING

Author: Kenny K.
Content: Best pizza I have ever had Â I had to start talking tattoo artists with the waitress though to get any kind of hospitality Â But I guess its Chicago and not KY

Author: Gfiddy F.
Content: Did not really know that pizza could be so thoroughly delicious

Author: Erin M.
Content: This is my alltime favorite pizza Â It is deep but not quite as deep as Giordanos Â It has less cheese than traditional deep dish which is a nice change of pace Â The best part is the crunchy crispy crust that is carmelized Â I recommend eatingin as the crust loses some crunchiness in delivery

Author: Marissa M.
Content: The pizza is delicious I got a pan pepperoni The breaded mushrooms were probably the best Ive had The employees are friendly and attentive theres like 5000 of them I cant think of any reason to give Pequods lower than a 5

Author: Brian A.
Content: I really like the pepperoni they use on the pizza here Â Great flavor Â Also love the caramelized crust Â I think it tastes better eaten at the restaurant then delivery as I like my pizza piping hot

Author: Furry P.
Content: I adore the carmelized crust pizza Â  Usually we get it delivered but decided to go on a Saturday night after a movie at Webster place Â We almost didnt go in because the place looked so small and crowded with people sitting outside on benches we thought the wait would be long Â DONT LET THE APPEARANCE OF A CROWD DISSUADE YOU Â We walked up to the hostess who promptly whisked us off to a table upstairs in a second enourmous dining room Â The place is seriously huge

Author: Chuck T.
Content: Good pizza decent bar Try it youll like it Not the best but a fine choice They have a bar get a beer some pizza watch the game USA

Author: Art K.
Content: Ordered a deep dish with pepperoni sausage and onions Â This pie was OUTSTANDING Â The big chunks of sausage and thick slices of pepperoni were really delicious Â The gooey cheesey crust was great was well Delivery was ontime Â Price was a little stiff at 28 for a large three topping Â I only wish they would have been as generous with the onions as they were with the pepperoni

Author: Rachel P.
Content: Ive never actually been to the restuarant but have gotten pizza delivered from here many times Â This is a review strictly of the pizza and not the restuarantserviceThis pizza ties with Lou Maltnatis as best pizza in Chicago IMHO at least The crust is thick and soft and carmelized with cheese around the outside Peperoni has a nice flavor peperoni and onion toppings are highly recommended Â The pizza is very filling I can eat 2 pieces if Im absolulety starving Â However as far as reheating the next day this pizza tastes the best hands down Crust and cheese holds up well and it just tastes great

Author: Jim S.
Content: Pequods is stellar pizza and an excellent deal Â I mean you get a huge personal deep dish pizza with one topping and a draft beer yes a beer during lunch hours for 5 Â Thats absurd Â The pizza is legit the scene is legit and I quickly became a regular here during lunch hours and had to walk a mile and a half each way to get here Â I miss you Pequods

Author: Mary F.
Content: I love Pequods Â Disclaimer giving Â 4 stars instead of 5 Â  I only ever get the pan pizzaIve been eating Pequods for years and always love it Â Pan pizza w sausage pan pizza w jalepenos pan pizza plain  greatI do miss the old interior  but the pizza is still the same and thats great

Author: Bobby C.
Content: This placeHANDS DOWNhas the best Pan Pizza I HAVE ever hadso far The two person booths are very comfortable and the service was average

Author: Arvind A.
Content: Not your typical pizza in Chicago Â Excellent crispy crust light amount of sauce and the amount of toppings were double than what I expected

Author: J. L.
Content: I like this better than Ginos and Lou Malnatis Â The crust is thick but not too dense or too dry Â They slather it in sauce cheese and whatever toppings you order Â We get mushrooms and sausage and there is no slice that is lacking large chunks of sausageI am giving it 4 stars because the wait for a table is loooooong then you have to wait 45min for the pizza to cook Â If they had more seating I would definitely give it 5 starsDont bother with the thin crust pizza thats not why you eat pizza in Chicago

Author: Shawn J.
Content: I give Pequods three stars for the beer selection and sandwiches I have experienced their pizza while dining in and while it was ok the next day for left overs was horrible I know a few people who love this pizza however it is really not one of my favorites The crust is more of a corn bread type crust and just doesnt suit my fancy The sauce the toppings everything else about the pizza was good I have had a meatball as well as a sausage from Pequods and they were terrific Would return for a sandwich and a beer

Author: Aaron L.
Content: 45 Deep Dish 12 Sausage Onions 12 Pepperoni Mushrooms

Author: Ron S.
Content: I think Pequods has decent pizza but I dont enjoy it as much as everyone raves about it The reason I give it 3 stars and not 4 is because I am not a fan of their crust because its really doughy However you still gotta go check it out for yourself even though this would probably be low on my list to grab some za

Author: Cam B.
Content: Best pizza in the city in my opinion Pan style is all I get and it is AMAZING Carmelized crust and all Never have drink specials and wings are disappointing but the pizza is so damn good I dont even care

Author: Timmy T.
Content: Absolute best deepdish pan pizza in Chicago Caramelized crust adds some char flavor and saltiness but doesnt overwhelm the pizza itself Think Lou Malnatis times five LM x 5  awesome This is just Chicago pizza done right at an affordable price with an incredibly large serving of food A large pan and a few beers could easily feed a half dozen happy people

Author: donna y.
Content: Not a bad place for a group if you have a reservation I am a bit biased as I love pizza in general but this pizzerias pizzas sure have a good crunch the basic of a good pizza I also liked the ease of parking in the area for free Definitely returning to try some other toppings Â Good job Pequod

Author: Will T.
Content: OMGperfect Deep Dish Pizza Â Had the sausage pep and onions Â Buttery crust and gobs of sausage and pepperoni Â A total local hangout Â Met up with my buddy who lives in Wrigley Â What a great recommendation

Author: Kelly H.
Content: Best pizza in the city and probably the whole world since this is Chicago Lou Malnatis is a close second but the carmelized crust takes my heart

Author: Regina K.
Content: You should only ever eat pizza from here Â Great beer good service sometimes a wait incredible food Â Nice place for larger groups or a 24 people Â Whenever I bring someone new here they cant believe they havent eaten it before

Author: Debbie M.
Content: I absolutely LOVE the pizza here LOVE  thats saying something from a native Chicagoan Dont skip the crust  its so good

Author: Catlleya s.
Content: ok food n bar ambiance but terrible customer service especially saturday nightwaited 1 12 hr 2 b seated no reservation thats ok but d pizza was cold n burnedhow can u do that at d same timeappetizer came latewaiters take forever 2 serve a glass of water n refill should proactively offer it in d 1st placeparking is a problem

Author: Erin T.
Content: The most AMAZING crust in the city Â I absolutely LOVE their deep dish pizza Â My husband and I regular order from here and we have ate in their dining room a few times as well Â We typically get the pan pizza half cheese for me and half pepperoni for him Â I usually insist on the Pequods salad with house vingarette Â The salad is pretty average but the pizza is what knocks my socks off Â The crust has this crunchy parmesan taste Â It is SO unique and delicious Â My husband occasionally complains that the pizza doesnt have enough sauce Â However we never seem to remember to ask for more so I am not sure what their response would be if you requested it Â I really like the atmosphere when you dine in at Pequods Â It has a really relaxed almost bar feel Â For me its a tie between Lou Malnatis and Pequods for the best deep dish in Chicago

Author: K N.
Content: Best Deepdish Pizza Ever

Author: Greg B.
Content: Amazing Â Fresh tasty ingredients Â Everything is wellbalanced Â Its nearly impossible to say what the best pizza in Chicago is but this has to be up there on most peoples lists

Author: Carlos V.
Content: Best deep dish and thin crust in Chicago I discovered this place by word of mouth I havent stopped going If you like a sausy deep dish with a crusty cheesy edge then you have to try it out If you are a meat lover on your pizza then you have to try the sausage Although the place looks small on the outside There is plenty of room for a large gathering upstairsWhether you are a local or out of towner you have to stop by and try Pequods

Author: Amanda M.
Content: 45 Came back to take my bf after not being pleased last time but I assured him it was because he got delivery and was all the way from LP to downtown He was much pleased this time Had a 35 min wait due to NCAA game but service was great and assured us that once the game was over the wait would not be much longer Luckily since it was nice we waited outside Because of its busyness we had the option to have our pizza halfway prepared so we didnt have to wait even longer when we were seated While being a nice idea I think this attributed to me not as enjoying the pizza as much as the first time We ordered a medium pan 6 slices with green pepper and onion First there were not that many green peppers but I felt like the crust this time was just slightly a little more chewydense than last time which was perfect Nonetheless I still prefer this over all the chains especially Lous which I dont know why people love so much Â Pequods crust is so much better with a nice fresh burnt taste straight from the pan Their service is also one of my favorites They are extremely well staffed and efficient and not overly eager or in your face

Author: Elise F.
Content: Amazing

Author: Matt M.
Content: Wow Thats about all I can say pequods We had the deep dish and its far superior to malnatis or Giordanos Â This will definitely be added to my regular rotation

Author: JoJean C.
Content: Great pizzasome of the best weve ever had Â My husband is a Chicago native and there are a couple of musthaves when were back in the city Â Pizza is at the top of the list and this was outstanding Â We ordered the thin crust for our grandkids and that was good but the deep dish will be something we talk about for a long time Â Worth a tenhour drive

Author: Jacko J.
Content: Believe the hype It s pretty darn good Much better than Ginos but not quite Lous status

Author: Michael D.
Content: Love Pequods how can one not

Author: Skipper D.
Content: One of the better Chicago style restaurants in the city Â Great place on the North Side was really cool and punk before the fire and they did the remodeling Â Now the decor is slightly cookiecutteryuppie but the pizza and wait staff still ROCK

Author: Mark W.
Content: Really really good we had the large pepperoni deep dish which blows away pizza from the chicago mainstays malnatis ginos giordanos Pretty expensive though came to almost 60 for 2 pizzas

Author: Merrin P.
Content: Ive been here twice and each time weve gotten a solid pizza Â I love the crust Â The cheese on the pizza is great but there is nothing better than caramelized cheese on your crust Â Both times weve gotten pepperoni sausage and mushroom  all the ingredients are quite tasty though I have to say that the more I have sausage the more I dont like it that much but oh well Â Anyway theres not much more I can add to this place except to say that its a great place to go after a movie especially when its a later movie and you are absolutely famished by the end of it Â Weve seen some crappy movies recently so the pizza afterwards has definitely been the highlight Â The Miller Lite is also always cold and the perfect compliment to our pizza Â Enjoy

Author: Chris A.
Content: I always order the italian beef wcheese its awesome Â My girl always gets the pizza Ive tried it but Im not crazy about it Â The atmosphere is fun sports on the TV and the wait staff is very helpful

Author: Jeff Y.
Content: some of the best pizza in chicago even though its not chicago style deep dish basically a slightly thicker than normal pan pizza with gigantor toppings Â the mojo is in the caramelized crust though Â forget that stuffed crust nonsense this is probably the only pizza where the crust is the best part Â also pretty tasty delivered but i would definitely dinein if possible im not sure what the pantyfaced whale logo is all about but he makes a good pizza pie nonetheless

Author: Heather V.
Content: Pequods is no doubt my FAVORITE pizza in Chicago Â Especially when Im in the mood for a thin pepperonitheirs cant be beat Â And they have a great beer selection too

Author: Robert C.
Content: The pizza here was hyped up a lot so maybe thats why I was a little disappointed Overall it was really good but it wasnt like I was blown away I thought 17 and change for a medium cheese pizza deep dish was a little pricey

Author: Niraj P.
Content: By far my favorite pizza in the city The crust is delicious especially with a side of their ranch dressing and the toppings are equally yummy Im partial to the pepperoni but Ive had other toppings and theyve all been great The service is overall as friendly and efficient as youre going to find for a pizza place thats as busy as it is If you havent tried this yet go for it

Author: Joe T.
Content: This is by far my 1 deep dish pizza for Chicago as of yet Sauce Is sweet and tangy crust is crisp and buttery and there signaturethe carmelized cheese crustis sex in your mouth

Author: R O.
Content: The Good The absolute BEST deep dish pizza I have EVER had Great service waiterswaitresses are fun and friendlyRecommended by more Chicagoans I know than any other place when asked where to go for the BEST pizzaThe Bad NoneThe UglyFriend told me he had food poisoning from them once to give you an idea of how good the pizza is he still goes there regularly

Author: Tamara U.
Content: Pequods is amazing My honey took me here when I was pregnantneedless to say he made many more trips within that nine months I am a fan for lifethe caramelized crust is divine I would recommend it to anyone who wants amazingly delicious pizzahands down the best Ive tasted in chitown matter of fact I think Ill call them on my way home and have some pizza for dinneryum

Author: Anik S.
Content: Yes Pequods you are awesomeNo frills atmosphere but the deep dish pizza with caramelized crust  giardiniera peppers is money total Fing moneyTo boot they have a lunch deal that includes a personal sized pie  1 beer or soda for 5 for dine inScrew all the chains and their supposed best Chicago style deep dishIf you have not been here yet and call yourself a Chicagoan  Id get here ASAP via your Cta CardIgoCarSegwayBicycleLegs nowWhy are you still reading this  go

Author: Dave A.
Content: best deep dish in chicago Â period Â if i were a rich man when i when to pequods i would order a large pepperoni with onion and then just eat the outside 1 Â that caramelized crust is the best Â and the giant sausage chunks are pretty damn good too Â yeah sure even every once in a while you get just an ok pizza Â and its not a dive like it was 5 years ago Â and sure it takes 45 minutes per pizza Â and the lines are long Â but its worth it Â i will go to the grave defending pequods as the best deep dish in chicago Â get take out or delivery if you must but its never the same as in the store Â and enjoy

Author: Janis S.
Content: Caramelized cheese crust so freakin good My favorite pizza in Chicago  I recommend the deep dish with pepperoni and pepperoncini Thin is still good but the deep dish is what you need to get Plus its deep dish that isnt solid cheese ie Ginos so youre not quite as full after you eat it

Author: David G.
Content: Great place for a bite to eat before a movie The crubled sausage and basil deep dish pizza is AWESOME Might be my favorite pizza joint in the cityIf you are going to a movie however do a pizza order call ahead and when you check in tell them you have a movie time otherwise they dont put the pie in the oven until your table is ready

Author: Jason C.
Content: This place deserves a 5 rating as I love the za and have been several times Â However last Saturday night I took my parents and soontobe inlaws for a casual dinner Â We had 830 reservations  didnt get seated till 915 Â The temperature was about 90 degrees  come on get some AC  its July in Chicago Â Pizza was great as usual but get the service and AC to match it

Author: Jim D.
Content: I was a little worried about moving away from my traditional pizza joints when I ordered from Pequods the first timebut that quickly went away when i tasted my first bite of this most tasty treat Â I love the pizza here and it has quickly become my favorite in the city Â Nothing better than a pepperoni pan pizza with that delicious caramelized crust Â MMMMM

Author: Nicholas W.
Content: Usually I prefer thin crust but I always go deep dish here It is the best in Chicago Giordanos has nothing on Pequods

Author: Mark A.
Content: The bar is nice  old school with movie posters good TVs and a shitload of blackhawks gear Â Beer selection is great with crafts and mainstream Â Came here on a Sunday for the 2nd half of a bears game Â Asked for the drink special which was 450 312 drafts Â Sorry thats not a special Â 12 buckets of bud light is a special Â  4 Hacker Pschorr is a special Â 450 for a pint of a beer brewed down the street is not a special Â Ordered a medium deep dish pie with intentions of leftovers Â It was delivered in the iron cast pan and it was delicious  especially the carmelized blackened cheese crust Â I wrapped up a couple pieces for the following night and went on my wayThrew 2 pieces in the oven to heat up the next day and was incredibly disappointed Â The crust becomes so thick and doughy and dry its almost impossible to eat without dipping it in a bowl of sauce Â I had to start eating backwards from the delicious crust still delicious as leftovers and throwing the rest away once it was goneI did note a ridiculous MF lunch special  less than 5 for a 7 inch pan pizza and a sodapint of Miller Lite Â Pizza is good bar is good leftovers are NOT Â Order a pie that you know will finish bc the leftovers will change your opinionIll go back but will order a size smaller

Author: Lauren K.
Content: As someone whos born and raised in Chicago Im surprised that so many people like this place Â I feel like Im eating bread covered with tomato sauce and a tiny bit of cheese Yuck Definitely wayyyy more places Id rather eat then pizza from this place

Author: Maria C.
Content: Made a reservation at Pequods for my birthday and the staff was more than accomdating for all 15 of us Â The pizzas took a while to come out and they actually forgot to put in our one thin crust we orderedbut absolutely well worth the wait and they took off 50 of the pizza they forgot aboutI actually almost forgot the negative experience because I enjoyed the food so muchAs for the pizza its amazingfrom the crispy caramalized cheese crust to the delicious sauce and endless toppingsits perfection on a plate The pizza differs from Lous or a Ginos which is much appreciated It was so refreshing to find a place like this and not too far away I will gladly return again and again

Author: Elaina C.
Content: This is my favorite pizza joint Â Being from the east coast I dont love deep dish and theirs is a little different than others Ive tried here less heavy and tastier Â On weekends they will let you make a reservation but it doesnt get you a table right away Â You just get priority over the people who have just walked in Â But you can put your pizza order in while you wait since it takes so long to cook anywaySide note I chose this as my last solid meal before getting my wisdom teeth out Â Must be my favorite meal

Author: Joshua D.
Content: Pizza came out undercooked and even when they redid it still tasted kind of bland Still take Lou Malnatis or the original UnoDue any day Nice change of pace though

Author: Bada Bing L.
Content: Far out man Â Their deep dish pizza is amongst the greats in the biz Â Super filling slices of all the good ingredients you could possibly want Â The intentionally burnt back crust trumps any pizza innovation that the mad scientists at pizza hut or dominos could ever come up with

Author: Sarah S.
Content: Yum Pizza crust was delish Sausage Pepperoni and Green olives on top I highly suggest it Can you tell I love salt

Author: James D.
Content: I rarely rate anything a 5 star but htis pizza is THAT good Â Love the deep dish wth big chunks of frsh veggies Â They carmelize the cheese on the edges of the za a real treat

Author: Jackie V.
Content: The Best Pizza in Chicago Def my fav  The Weekends get packed expect a 3045 min wait but its sooo worth it

Author: Omar E.
Content: Great Pizza Â I just wished that their beer selection would be better

Author: Matt C.
Content: Ive been coming here for 5 years Â and I have not once had a bad pizza here Â There is something about the pan w sausage Â It is very simple but always outstanding Â Pequods is easily my go to for pan pizza

Author: John E.
Content: Best deep dish in Chicago as far as Im concerned Â Can say that I havent had any thin crust pizza better than Pequods as well Â Great place to eat too  staff is very friendly and service is great Â Have been there many times and always a great experience Â Delivery is excellent as well Â Cant miss with this place

Author: Jl G.
Content: Going here for years before the yuppies took over but this place still my spot for pizza Sausage is flame stop order it and go deep dish Â Packed on the weekend so enjoy

Author: Sandy G.
Content: Its the only deep dish pizza I will eatlove it Â They carmelize the crust like no other Â Really puts other pizzerias to shame

Author: Eric S.
Content: Our group came away with mixed reviews about the place however those that didnt like the place as much are thin crust fans I personally loved the pizza I had it on Saturday and I kept thinking about sunday night and even today monday We ordered a Large Pan Pizza with Sausage Canadian Bacon and Tomatoes The ingredients where top notch Everyone agreed on that The crust is thick however the bread isnt very dense I thought it was great other thought it was too much bread but they are thin crust fans Most enjoyed the burnt crust and cheese

Author: Tracy C.
Content: My favorite pizza ever of all time Seriously its the best Get the deep dish and you will not be disappointed

Author: Kim S.
Content: Best pizza ever I have all my out of town friends and family hooked on this Â Every time they come to see me we always have to go to pequods Â Make sure you order the deep dish though Â Otherwise you may not get the full pizza bliss experience

Author: Kelly C.
Content: Obviously the pan pizza is the way to go at this pizza place Â The caramelized crust is just superb Â Get ready for some large toppings because they come in chunks Â Yum I just ordered it and I cant wait for it to be delivered

Author: Gerald A.
Content: Im not a fan of the caramelized burned and rubbery cheese on the crust The sauce was plentiful without being too acidic and making me regret eating one piece too manyBut overall the meal was forgettable I think Id try every other deep dish place in Chicago before looping back to this one

Author: Ro S.
Content: My family loves Pequods Â It is one of their favorite pizza companies of all times I have been on the fence for awhile because I was not sure if I really did enjoy their caramelized signature crust I used to think it was too burnt for my likingYesterday on a Saturday I ordered a small pan pizza with garlic and spinach for take out Service The place was packed but when I made my way to the order desk they had several people on hand to assistServing size My roommate and I shared the small pan pizza and it was the right am amount of food without overeating and we were pretty hungry to begin withThis pizza smelled amazing I was tempted on the ride home to take a bite but I resistedWhen I took a bite at home I was speechless The caramelized crust is ingenious and really gives the pizza a delicious and unique taste They are now in my top 3 favorite pizza places of all times If you have not tried it do it

Author: Grant H.
Content: The pizza here is fantastic Heres whyThe toppings are greatThe crust has an awesome buttery crispness on the bottomThe caramelized cheese around the edges is outofthisworldJust go here now Do it You wont be disappointed

Author: Brian S.
Content: Pizza is pretty good however their staff and service is downright horrible Ordered delivery and not the whole order arrived and when asked when we can get it the delivery driver started giving me attitude and talking back to me Called in to get it corrected and the person taking orders started giving me attitude as well Such a shame good food gets overshadowed by horrible service

Author: David G.
Content: To me this place is unique amongst the Chicago style pizza places Â The burnt ring around the edge of the pizza really adds something different and somehow it actually worksIve only been here for lunch Â They run a great deal at 5 for a personal size pizza and a drink Â You can even get a beer if you wish for that priceThe veggie toppings Ive tried have always been fresh and Ive never had a bad pizza here Â I wish it was a little closer to the el but its worth the walk or short cab ride from the North Clybourn stop

Author: Max S.
Content: Good deep dish Really thickfluffy crust A noble attempt of capturing the true Chicagostyle pizza

Author: PB M.
Content: Great pizza fun place lots of TVs and great pizza cant say that enoughCan get slammed and crowded so not a lot of room to stand around and wait but its so good it doesnt really matter

Author: Hannah R.
Content: Best pie ever Seriously unbelievable I traveled to Chicago from Texas for pizza and I was NOT disappointed Excellent draft beer selection and service to boot I am extremely satisfied and I have leftovers too

Author: Dustin N.
Content: The best around the rest are just chains

Author: George G.
Content: Ive been going here my whole life Best deep dish there is If youre in Chicago go here often

Author: Ellay B.
Content: Omg this is the best pizza I have ever had I have been here a few times before and whenever Im in Chicago I come here Both deep dish and thin crust are amazing and they deliver till 3 in the morning which is awesome I have been to other pizza places in Chicago but nothing beats pequods

Author: Wes H.
Content: My Dad and I decided to take a trip up to watch our beloved Cardinals take on the Cubs and check out a pizza joint After looking on Yelp we decided that Pequods would be the place to go After having Pizzeria Uno taken from us here in St Louis we were itching for a solid deep dish WOW This place is amazing The price was just right and next time I go with one other person Ill still get a large because it was great to bring back home Ive already recommended it to anyone and everyone that livesvisits Chicago Ill be back

Author: Tom T.
Content: Im a fanatical fan of Chicago deep dish now Sauce was great toppings were great nicely blackened crust great stuff

Author: Evelia M.
Content: This is our go to place when it comes to Pizza Their deep dish is crazy delicious Their prices are just as good They also have a lunch special for 5 You get your individual deep dish plus a pop AMAZING We have been coming here since forever my mom has been going there since before your truly was born I took my son there and he approved 14 month old   so this one is a keeper for generations for sure

Author: Dan M.
Content: Just wanted to add that I love this place

Author: Heather R.
Content: THE best pizza in Chicago We dont even bother with any other deep dish places anymore This is our only optionLove everything about it The carmelized cheesy crust sauce toppingsThe upstairs area is so much more appealing now after the renovation They have plenty of seating now and 2 full bars Perfect place to go before a movie at Webster Place

Author: mike p.
Content: The best pizza Ive ever had in Chicago The caramelized crust tastes great and the saucecheese they use is amazing I love Pequods

Author: Travis A.
Content: The service here SUCKS in fact Ive had better service from a gas station attendant My wife and went in for lunch today the managerhost was on a personal cell phone call and acknowledged us by holding up two fingers to indicate the size of our party He then proceeded to take us all the way to the back of the establishment and seat us at a table next to the kitchen door Still on his phone It was not until he ended his call that he answered her Â and our request to be seated at another table Which he then said he had something to do in the kitchen handed us the menus and told us to sit where we wanted and he would be right back I failed to mention that the restaurant was practically empty maybe 12 to 15 diners tops I will make it a point to tell everyone I know not to dine in at this place Note to staff WORK ON YOUR MANNERS

Author: David A.
Content: The best deep dish pizza in Chicago the slightly burnt butter crisp crust is phenomenal and accompanied ingredients of cheese sauce and topping are balanced perfectly my favorite and recommended toppings are pepperoni onions fresh tomatoes black olives with garlic it is just pizza heaven check it out for yourself and Enjoy

Author: Colin U.
Content: Oh PequodsI wont care what you are doing to my arteries if you keep treating my stomach this way Â OM NOM NOM

Author: Vivian R.
Content: Been going to Pequads for years When the old Great Ace was across the street from them I used to go over there after work with coworkersSo when you get a good pan pizza its the best thing but sometimes go back and it sucksIt hit or miss with them mainly stingy with toppings xtra is xtra  nothing is for nothing been there slogan raise your prices and if the pie is worth it greatif not oh well

Author: Ryan M.
Content: Im surprised this doesnt have five stars Its the best pan pizza in the city More dough less sauce than most others but thats why I like it The carmelized crust makes it the most unique in the city Start with the jalapeno poppers Finish with pan pepperoni And youll go home a VERY happy person

Author: Dani B.
Content: I have been going to Pequods regularly now for almost 13 years and have nothing but good things to say about their pizza Im not sure in all of that time I have even tried anything there BUT their pizza The thin is always great and the deep dish is fantastic I liked the place better before they remodeled it had more personality but its still nice to eat there Hands down still the best pizza Ive had in Chicago

Author: Colin O.
Content: This is easily the best pizza in the city Â From the caramelized crust down to the sauce it doesnt get any better Â Or does itOh yeah 5 lunch special every week day a personal pan pizza with one topping and one free fountain drink or Miller Lite Â Im not a big fan of Miller Lite but when I pay 5 for a pizza and a beer its hard to beat

Author: Jody C.
Content: Great thin or pan Â pizza Â The lunch special from 113 Mon to Fri is a fabulous deal Less than 5 for a beer or soft drink and an individual pan pizza

Author: Aimee M.
Content: This was my first experience at Pequods with the Windy City Pizza Club We sat upstairs which was semi busy The atmosphere was nice easy to hear the people next to you but the lighting could have been a little better The menu was not as big as I expected for this being a very well known pizza establishment The pizza was very good I had a thin crust with vegetables but the service was terrible We ordered our food and after awhile we asked the waitress how much longer it would be till we were served She went to go check and then told us that there was a mixup in the kitchen and that we would have to wait a few more minutes we were starving at this point so not words we wanted to hear Overall I would go back but maybe not at a busy time of the day

Author: D S.
Content: I went there with the Windy City Pizza Club Â The crust delivered its well known taste but I thought the medium pan was a little heavy on the sauce compared to what I remember the last time I went there Â Prices were very reasonable The service was very friendly and I found my drink continually refilled up until the time the check came and then the waitress vanished Â I would recommend trying it at least once because it is very unique and good but dont plan to go back there for a while

Author: Jacob a.
Content: Ive been living in the area near peaquod for about 6 months now I am so glad that there is a good pizza place in walking distance Peaquods is my top two favorite pan pizzas My roommates go there at least once a week the staff is terrific and Its a good place to watch sports games while you eat

Author: Steve V.
Content: The crust is fing delicious The whole pie was still really good good enough that I have ordered it several more times But if I could cross breed pequods crust with a Lou malnatis pizza it would be the greatest pie in the world Definitely try it and make your own judgement

Author: Geoff D.
Content: With over 700 reviews there isnt much else to say other than that Pequods is the best pan pizza Ive ever had The caramelized cheese around the crust the sauce the pepperoni  all absolutely fantastic

Author: Ami T.
Content: This place is amazingI am not sure what is up with the whale with the thong on its face but the pizza is heavenlyThey bake their pan pizza in a cast iron pan so the cheese gets burnt on the bottommight sound gross but its really goodThe staff their is really nice and patient I recommend getting garlic on your pizza it adds a little kick

Author: K T.
Content: Small place Great pizzas

Author: Andrew M.
Content: Do not let the humble exterior of this restaurant fool you  the pizza here is absolutely fantasticA few friends and I stopped by here last night before our movie across the street Talk about conveniently located We were hesitant to check it out at first because the outside makes it look a bit run down Imagine our surprise when we found that Pequods is not only nice inside it is ENORMOUSThe menu is simple and straightforward You can tell that pizza is their specialty Why bother with a large extravagant menu when you can instead concentrating on perfecting one dish Thats not to say there werent appetizerssides on the menu because there were We just elected to ignore themThe pizza was absolutely PHENOMENAL We stuck to a simple large pepperoni pizza It was one of the best pizzas I have had since moving to Chicago 3 years ago The large pizza thin crust was easily enough for 4 or 5 people The best highlight of the evening was when the bill arrived A large pizza 3 sodas and a salad came up to 30Youd better believe Ill be returning to Pequods VERY soon

Author: Anne R.
Content: Really good pizzathin crust or deep dish Â Went there with a bunch of people after a game and they were accommodating Â Went back for a few drinks after a date and it was still good Â However parking is sketchy around there

Author: Lauren M.
Content: This is our goto pizza place Â My favorite deep dish in the City Â And the owner and servers are so nice and hospitable Â My husband and I just love coming here

Author: Ashley H.
Content: Best pizza in Chicago And very cold Blue Moon on draft Inside is much nicer than the outside GO AND ENJOY

Author: Carlo B.
Content: The first time I ate Pequods was when we had staff meeting at a clinic I used to work at Â At first I was wondering what the char was on the crust Im not questioning why but what is it Â My boss said it was cheese and that made it even better Â Their pizza was very unique thin crust attributes accidental caramel crust loaded looking with the appeal of a stuffed pie the more to love deal Â It was good good enough to realize that I sometimes forget that it was a deep dish Â However to me the only thing that really got me interested in their pizza was the crust Â The cheese peeledfell off often that forced me to reset most of the pizza back on the crust Â And because of caramelizing the crust was very soggy underneath Â Either way interesting concept tasty but hard to overlook the flaws when you actually eat it

Author: Emily B.
Content: Best deep dish pizza Ive ever had The caramelized cheese crust was delicious Also the salad we ordered had cheese on it cut into the shape of whales an obvious nod to Moby Dick I love it

Author: Penny D.
Content: I forgot I had negatively reviewed Pequods in the past Their delivery continues to be horrible but eating at the restaurant is amazing Their pizza is one of the best in the city Both the deep dish and the thin crust are so good although I dont love the burnt cheese edges like everyone else does So good Love eating at Pequods Worth the wait

Author: Al G.
Content: Fantastic Pizza I love there signature deep dish pizza with the burnt cheesy edges Â This is one of the BEST places for pizza in Chicago The atmosphere is fine for beers and a relaxing friendly night out Great deals all week long Please go when you get a chance Heck make an outing just for Pequods

Author: Charles S.
Content: Let me start off by saying I consider my self a pizza guy Before I ate at Pequods I considered Lous as the best Chicago style pizza in town While I still love Lous I will move that title to Pequods This place is amazing My buddy Rich introduced me to this gem one night and the rest is history I havent eaten deep dish pie anywhere else since After I had it the first time I had cheese I thought wow this pizza is great The second time I had their sausage and green pepper even better Since then I have ordered it several times and it has been just as good every time Even their delivery is excellent The pie comes to my house steaming hot and I live in the loop which is a fair distance from the Lincoln Park location Anyway I can go on but let me just say it is the BEST pizza anywhere Try this place you will feel the same way Enjoy

Author: Alisha O.
Content: Get the deepdish Â Dont bother with anything else on the menu this is the only thing that matters but its handsdown the best in the city Â The best anywhere in my opinion

Author: sharon s.
Content: The pizza was just fantasticmy brother inlaw said we had to try it so we went early on a saturday nite  It was just starting to get busy but we were able to get a nice cozy booth for twoUnfortunatley our waitress did not have much of a personalitybut the pizza defininatly speaks for itselfThe crust was just dark enough the body was lite and airy the sauce was full of flavor and the cheese was browned to perfection this place is a winner in my book looking forward to going back

Author: Kelsey O.
Content: Best Pizza in Chicago hands down I am a pizza lover so when I was told about Pequods two years ago I couldnt wait to put it to the test If Im out seeing a movie it is at the Webster Theatre which is right across the street so a pizza and movie night is perfect for me I have read that some people think they have too much crust but I disagree Its delicious and the way it is served each piece remains hot Another thing Pequods is so reasonably priced Worth every penny They will even hold your leftovers for you until you get out of the movie

Author: chris e.
Content: My favorite pizza in Chicago The caramelized over cooked crust is super delicious If youre tired of cornmeal crust this is definitely for you I cant think of a better winter food in Chicago

Author: Jake F.
Content: Weve been to Pequods a few times and I am finally writing a review Â This is Chicago pizza Â Be prepared to wait however because everyone knows about this place Â I recommend making a reservation Â You will still wait but at least there is hope Â The pizza itself is a terrific deepdish that comes out hot from the oven Â The place is beyond packed but they have a secret upstairs that I just found out about Â Give it a try for great Chicago pizza

Author: Mike P.
Content: Great pizza and great atmosphere Â You cant go wrong ordering a pizza from Pequods and watching hockey

Author: Amourena C.
Content: omg if you want chicago style pizza you absolutelt can NOT beat pequads Best deep dish eva

Author: Mike T.
Content: After a late night meeting we decided to go to Pequods recently due to good recommendationsI recall maybe going to this place years ago but I cant remember Â Maybe it was another pizza place nearbyWe ordered bruscetta for our appetizer which was very good Â The perfect portions for the two of us Â We ordered a sausagemushroom pizza which was a great pizza among one of my favorites around Chicago Â Wash it down with a cold beer and that makes me happy

Author: Brandy W.
Content: Pequods is my favorite deep dish in the city Â Its next to Webster Place Theater so often a goto before or after a movie In fact thats girls night this week Â Its a really big restaurant with lots of TVs Its roomy and lively Â There is a main floor and upstairs I like the upstairs the best Â The deep dish is delicious Yum I love the sauce and the crust I like getting extra sauce

Author: D W.
Content: Excellent pizza I do like their deep dish Good sauce not too cheesy One of the few pizza places where I have cravings for the pizza I usually get a cheese pizza or with spinach on it easy on the cheese Atmosphere is nothing too special The table placement is a bit tight unless you are at one of the tall tables in the front Beer selection is ok service is good

Author: Jason G.
Content: Id give this place many more stars but I only enjoy their food when I can get it Â I just cant grasp why the delivery area changes Â I have ordered from them before and they have delivered when I call they ask if this is my name and my address because I have ordered from them before Â I called Sunday night spoke with whomever picked up the phone putting me on hold without putting me on hold Â So now I can hear everyone talking in the back and people saying I dont see why we wouldnt deliver there Â Now a manager gets on the phone and tells me sorry we cant deliver to you Â Why Ive been delivered to before Â Because we have to keep our customers happy Wait what I am calling just to talk and see how your Sunday night is going Â Nope I am calling for PIZZA So when I said I wouldnt ever order from them again guess what Â The woman manager said OK Â Guess you guys must pride yourself on customer service Thanks for the past pizza pies Pequods but I am in the service industry myself and everyone I talk to about pizza will never go in and patronize your place again

Author: Ted S.
Content: Best Pan pizza in Chicago

Author: Dave Y.
Content: Fantastic Pizza Â Took the whole family and were treated very well Â Even the 4 year old loved the deep dish cheese pizza Â Great servers and fun environment Â Be prepared to wait for a bit for the pizza but once it gets there you wont be disappointed Â We were looking for a great Chicago style pizza and we found it Â Reasonable prices and easy parking

Author: Kevin K.
Content: Pequodswhy did it take me soooo long to find you Â Our first date was slightly off when I was told it was the best pizza out there only to be taken by a friend to get the thin crust pizza Â That was then and this is now when I stumbled back in and experienced the REAL deal DEEP dish pizza Â Yumyum Â Can you say carmellized crustthats right the crust is consistently and deliciously always carmelized in Pequods fashion Â This is a tough choice as there are many options in the area but my crown goes to Pequods for the best deep dish za in all of Chicago Â Go for the pizza and stay for the beers

Author: Sarah S.
Content: Great food and service that Id recommend to anyone

Author: Matt B.
Content: Great pizza and the wait staff was very courteous We went to dinner at 6 on a Saturday and there was no wait Around 630 the place started getting really packed so we got there at a great time Our only complaint is that we were at a middle hightop table and when it got packed people surrounded around the bar which was right next to our table Other than that I highly recommend it

Author: John E.
Content: Best deep dish pizza I have ever had Hands down No question

Author: Chris A.
Content: Best Deep Dish pizza I have ever had

Author: Daniel R.
Content: First time trying Pequods tonight Amazing We will definitely be back

Author: Libby T.
Content: This was my first stop for deep dish pizza when I went to Chicago We had a big group of 16 and they were very accommodating we did call ahead We ordered 4 large pizzas for the group with a variety of toppings and it was more than enough The pizza was delish although I thought for deep dish pizza the toppings were underneath the sauce but here they put them on top The crust is the real deal here They bake it in a cast iron pan and the crust is perfectly done I also had deep dish pizza again on my trip and I found that I liked the inside of the pizza better elsewhere but this place is definitely worth trying They also have good local beers here so make you sure you try some of those

Author: Keith S.
Content: Had a deep dish large pizza with 2 friends Â It took about 40 minutes to arrive on a Sunday night was busy and worth the wait Â The pizza was excellent with great flavor and ingredients Â We could only eat half so come hungry

Author: Zack C.
Content: The pizza was delightful It was better than that of other deep dish establishments in Chicago

Author: Michael L.
Content: Cool place decent pizza

Author: Ji K.
Content: My heart hurt while eating this pizza and not for reasons you would think Having read fellow Yelpers reviews I had extremely high expectations for Pequods pizza Â But sadly sadly sadly this pizza is so very overrated So in addition to my heart the hurt spread to my head because I couldnt quite fathom why this pizza is so beloved It is a ridiculously thick slab of unappetizing crust so much so that I sliced most of the bottom half off followed by a nearly nonexistent layer of cheese slathered with sweet chunky sauce which was probably the only good thing and finished off with a meager sprinkling of your topping of choice Oh I forgot to mention that the outer edge of the crust is lined with black burnt cheese which they call caramelized cheese crust but this can easily be achieved by throwing mozzarella parmesan or your preferred cheese on a hot skillet and letting it sit there until it burns I adore pizza Really truly utterly adore pizza I do not know what this round concoction was It broke my heart made me unjustifiably fatter and took 20 of hardearned money that could have been spent on something more worth it

Author: Mike G.
Content: I love Chicago and I love chicago pizza and although I grew up in Chicago I havent lived here in may years but I do get back on a semi regular basis Â Whenever I come to town I love to go to Pizzeria Uno Â The problem with Unos though is that it is small and hard to get a table in a decent amount of time and the more people in your party the harder it is and longer it takes Â This being said I started to hear great things about Pequods Â I have to tell you I was skeptical at first because like I said I am a Pizzeria Unos fanatic Â I am so glad that we decided to check out Pequods this last trip Â 5 of us went for lunch and we were walked through the bar which looked very cool and taken upstairs Â My first thought was this sucks I hate being put into an overflow room but I found out that this is where most of the seating really is Â Because it was lunch we all ordered the killer lunch deal that they offer Â This is a one topping 7 personal pizza and it was served with either a beer or a soft drink for only 499 what a deal I still thought because of the price it was going to be a watered down version of the real thing Â Boy was I wrong Â Small but awesome is what I say now Â We each orderd different styles Â I had sausage mushroom extra 95 additional toppings green pepper and it was loaded with toppings and a really nice quality sausage Â Everyone at the table thougt that they ordered the best pizza and every one of us walked away with a smile and a full belly Â I did notice a few tables with a full size pizza and I have to admit that they looked unbelievable and cant wait to go back Â I have told a few people that this is now my new 1 and will be my go to pizza joint whenever I get back to town Fun atmosphere attentive wait staff and Â GREAT PIZZA All makes this a dont miss stop Look at the pictures drool and then make your way over here as soon as you can and have what I now think is the best pizza in town

Author: Peter H.
Content: we get the pan pizza with pepperoni usually and some pepperoncinis as well try that outgood mozarella sticks and house salad as well i enjoy this place

Author: Kayel O.
Content: I finally got to try Pequods the other day after I caught a movie I heard so much about it so it was about time Â AMAZING Â Amazing pizza Great service Definitely coming in one day for the lunch special

Author: M M.
Content: they have their good days and off dayssometimes the pizza is GREATother times its like a totally different crew is making them  Id like to see more consistencey I do love their pies though

Author: theresa k.
Content: definately worthwhile if you are looking for something different when it comes to pizza they make their pizza crust from carmelized cheese if you decide to dine youll find it roomy clean and nice widescreen televisions playing sports and awesome music channels thumbs up

Author: Casey M.
